Huahin Manager

Huahin Manager is Simple Hadoop MapReduce Job Management System.
Huahin can get a list of MapReduce jobs, get status, do a kill for the job.

Huahin Manager is distributed under Apache License 2.0.


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation
  http://huahin.github.com/huahin-manager/

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements
  * Java 6+

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install Huahin Manager
  ~ $ tar xzf huahin-manager-0.1.tar.gz

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Configure Huahin Manager

Edit the huahin-manager-0.1/conf/huahinManager.properties file and set mapred.job.tracker property to the JobTracker URI. For example:

  mapred.job.tracker=localhost:9001

When you change the boot port, edit the huahin-manager-0.1/conf/port file.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Start/Stop Huahin Manager

To start/stop Huahin Manager use Huahin Manager's bin/manager script. For example:

  $ bin/manager start

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Test Huahin Manager is working

  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/list"
[
  {
    "jobid": "job_201205111223_0001",
    "mapComplete": "100.0%",
    "name": "JOB_EBCF7626A41F34B4C7276DB2B152336F",
    "priority": "NORMAL",
    "reduceComplete": "100.0%",
    "schedulingInfo": "NA",
    "startTime": "Fri May 11 12:25:18 JST 2012",
    "state": "SUCCEEDED",
    "user": "huahin"
  }
]

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Huahin Manager REST APIs

Get all job list.
  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/list"

Get failed job list.
  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/list/failed"

Get killed job list.
  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/list/killed"

Get prep job list.
  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/list/prep"

Get running job list.
  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/list/running"

Get succeeded job list.
  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/list/succeeded"

Get job status.
  {JOBID} specifies the jobid.
  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/status/{JOBID}"

  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X GET "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/status/job_201205111223_0001"

Kill job for ID.
  {JOBID} specifies the job ID.
  ~ $ curl -X DELETE "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/kill/id/{JOBID}"

  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X DELETE "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/kill/id/job_201205111223_0001"

Kill job for job name.
  {JOBNAME} specifies the job name.
  ~ $ curl -X DELETE "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/kill/name/{JOBNAME}"

  For example:
  ~ $ curl -X DELETE "http://<HOOPHOSTNAME>:9010/job/kill/name/WORD_COUNT_JOB"
